Dmitry Galkovsky makes an interesting point about the Pioneer plaque, the Voyager musical record, etc. All this stuff is sent to space for "aliens" from another galaxy to discover, but it's obvious that the elites or "adults", people paying for it, know there are no aliens there.

It's obvious all this stuff sent to deep space is one day all going to be retrieved and brought back to earth and put in a museum here. It's not a message in a bottle for space aliens, it's a time capsule for mankind or even an object for potential future religious/ritual use.
